install.packages("devtools")","type":"ordered-list-item","depth":1,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"c6dkj","text":"Install the MLSTar package
devtools::install_github('iferres/MLSTar')","type":"ordered-list-item","depth":1,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"9qtag","text":"
","type":"ordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"2v1a2","text":"This package will only work "out of the box" with MLST schemes on the PubMLST database/website, so for other schemes (e.g Klebsiella on the Pasteur website) you need to download the profiles and allele sequences.
For klebsiella the profiles can be found 
https://bigsdb.web.pasteur.fr/cgi-bin/bigsdb/bigsdb.pl?db=pubmlst_klebsiella_seqdef
allele sequences can be found here
https://bigsdb.web.pasteur.fr/cgi-bin/bigsdb/bigsdb.pl?db=pubmlst_klebsiella_seqdef&page=downloadAlleles

I have pre-downloaded them and zipped them up here","type":"ordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"UNDERLINE","offset":255,"length":83},{"style":"UNDERLINE","offset":374,"length":104},{"style":"UNDERLINE","offset":526,"length":4}],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":255,"length":83},{"key":1,"offset":374,"length":104},{"key":2,"offset":526,"length":4}],"data":{}},{"key":"eff66","text":"Please noteIf providing your own profiles and sequences check that the header names in the profiles TSV match the names of the sequence file prefixes and that there are no trailing tabs in either the header or profile rows. 

e.g 
sed -i 's/[[:space:]]*$//'  kpn_profiles.txt","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":0,"length":11}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"7mccs","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"8rh7k","text":"on Mac OSX","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"d24ei","text":"sed -i '' 's/[[:space:]]*$//'  kpn_profiles.txt","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"9k48p","text":"Then to find the profiles and extract the sequences we run the following commands","type":"ordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"3uag4","text":"Find supported organisms
listPubmlst_orgs()","type":"ordered-list-item","depth":1,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"j589","text":"Find schemes for a supported organism
listPubmlst_schemes(org = "escherichia")
